South Africa May Produce 1.932 Million Tons of Sugar as Drought Breaks

-- B y   A l a s t a i r   R e e d   a n d   B r i a n   L a t h a m
-- 
2011-08-10T09:39:53Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-08-10/south-african-farmers-may-produce-1-932-million-tons-of-sugar-this-season.html
South Africa  may produce  1.932
million metric tons  of sugar in the 2011-2012 season, the South
African Sugar Association said on its website today.  Production is little changed from 1.909 million metric tons
in the 2010-2011 season, a company spokesman who can’t be
identified because of the association’s policy said in a phone
interview from Durban today.  South Africa may produce 2.1 million metric tons of sugar
in the 2012-2013 season as a result of improved rains, the
association said today.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Brian Latham in Johannesburg at 
 blatham@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Antony Sguazzin at 
 asguazzin@bloomberg.net . 